{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1119,"text":"You may have heard\nabout the Koran's idea of paradise"},{"time":4572,"text":"being 72 virgins,"},{"time":6875,"text":"and I promise I will come back\nto those virgins."},{"time":9852,"text":"But in fact, here in the Northwest,\nwe're living very close"},{"time":12830,"text":"to the real Koranic idea of paradise,"},{"time":15457,"text":"defined 36 times as \"gardens\nwatered by running streams.\""},{"time":21900,"text":"Since I live on a houseboat\non the running stream of Lake Union,"},{"time":26161,"text":"this makes perfect sense to me."},{"time":28407,"text":"But the thing is, how come\nit's news to most people?"},{"time":32707,"text":"I know many well-intentioned non-Muslims"},{"time":34900,"text":"who've begun reading\nthe Koran, but given up,"},{"time":37591,"text":"disconcerted by its \"otherness.\""},{"time":40912,"text":"The historian Thomas Carlyle\nconsidered Muhammad"},{"time":43664,"text":"one of the world's greatest heroes,"},{"time":45664,"text":"yet even he called the Koran"},{"time":48100,"text":"\"as toilsome reading as I ever undertook;\na wearisome, confused jumble.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":53490,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":55790,"text":"Part of the problem,\nI think, is that we imagine"},{"time":58820,"text":"that the Koran can be read\nas we usually read a book --"},{"time":62500,"text":"as though we can curl up\nwith it on a rainy afternoon"},{"time":65500,"text":"with a bowl of popcorn within reach,"},{"time":67500,"text":"as though God --"},{"time":69044,"text":"and the Koran is entirely in the voice\nof God speaking to Muhammad --"},{"time":72810,"text":"were just another author\non the best-seller list."},{"time":77675,"text":"Yet, the fact that so few people\ndo actually read the Koran"},{"time":81752,"text":"is precisely why it's so easy to quote --\nthat is, to misquote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87038,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":88086,"text":"Phrases and snippets taken out of context"},{"time":90500,"text":"in what I call the \"highlighter version,\""},{"time":92600,"text":"which is the one favored\nby both Muslim fundamentalists"},{"time":95711,"text":"and anti-Muslim Islamophobes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98996,"text":"So this past spring,"},{"time":100846,"text":"as I was gearing up to begin writing\na biography of Muhammad,"},{"time":104932,"text":"I realized I needed to read\nthe Koran properly --"},{"time":109190,"text":"as properly as I could, that is."},{"time":111976,"text":"My Arabic is reduced by now\nto wielding a dictionary,"},{"time":115110,"text":"so I took four well-known translations"},{"time":117500,"text":"and decided to read them\nside by side, verse by verse,"},{"time":121689,"text":"along with a transliteration\nand the original seventh-century Arabic."},{"time":128812,"text":"Now, I did have an advantage."},{"time":132483,"text":"My last book was about the story\nbehind the Shi'a-Sunni split,"},{"time":137175,"text":"and for that, I'd worked closely\nwith the earliest Islamic histories,"},{"time":140612,"text":"so I knew the events\nto which the Koran constantly refers,"},{"time":144398,"text":"its frame of reference."},{"time":146399,"text":"I knew enough, that is, to know\nthat I'd be a tourist in the Koran --"},{"time":151500,"text":"an informed one,"},{"time":153500,"text":"an experienced one, even,"},{"time":154999,"text":"but still an outsider,"},{"time":157372,"text":"an agnostic Jew reading\nsomeone else's holy book."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161218,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":163317,"text":"So I read slowly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164911,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":169420,"text":"I'd set aside three weeks\nfor this project,"},{"time":171931,"text":"and that, I think,\nis what is meant by \"hubris\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":174825,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179135,"text":"because it turned out to be three months."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181335,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":183246,"text":"I did resist the temptation\nto skip to the back,"},{"time":185768,"text":"where the shorter and more\nclearly mystical chapters are."},{"time":188959,"text":"But every time I thought I was beginning\nto get a handle on the Koran --"},{"time":192500,"text":"that feeling of \"I get it now\" --"},{"time":194806,"text":"it would slip away overnight,"},{"time":196893,"text":"and I'd come back in the morning,"},{"time":198571,"text":"wondering if I wasn't lost\nin a strange land."},{"time":202038,"text":"And yet, the terrain was very familiar."},{"time":205317,"text":"The Koran declares that it comes\nto renew the message"},{"time":208204,"text":"of the Torah and the Gospels."},{"time":209661,"text":"So one-third of it reprises\nthe stories of Biblical figures"},{"time":213173,"text":"like Abraham, Moses, Joseph, Mary, Jesus."},{"time":218741,"text":"God himself was utterly familiar"},{"time":221409,"text":"from his earlier manifestation as Yahweh,"},{"time":224500,"text":"jealously insisting on no other gods."},{"time":228638,"text":"The presence of camels, mountains,\ndesert wells and springs"},{"time":233726,"text":"took me back to the year I spent\nwandering the Sinai Desert."},{"time":237926,"text":"And then there was the language,\nthe rhythmic cadence of it,"},{"time":241500,"text":"reminding me of evenings spent\nlistening to Bedouin elders"},{"time":244745,"text":"recite hours-long narrative poems"},{"time":247746,"text":"entirely from memory."},{"time":250827,"text":"And I began to grasp why it's said"},{"time":255554,"text":"that the Koran is really\nthe Koran only in Arabic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260539,"text":"Take the Fatihah,\nthe seven-verse opening chapter"},{"time":264451,"text":"that is the Lord's Prayer\nand the Shema Yisrael of Islam combined."},{"time":269000,"text":"It's just 29 words in Arabic,"},{"time":272061,"text":"but anywhere from 65 to 72 in translation."},{"time":275926,"text":"And yet the more you add,\nthe more seems to go missing."},{"time":280867,"text":"The Arabic has an incantatory,\nalmost hypnotic quality"},{"time":285500,"text":"that begs to be heard rather than read,"},{"time":288782,"text":"felt more than analyzed."},{"time":291245,"text":"It wants to be chanted out loud,"},{"time":293328,"text":"to sound its music in the ear\nand on the tongue."},{"time":296755,"text":"So the Koran in English\nis a kind of shadow of itself,"},{"time":301500,"text":"or as Arthur Arberry called his version,"},{"time":304355,"text":"\"an interpretation.\""},{"time":307500,"text":"But all is not lost in translation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310800,"text":"As the Koran promises,\npatience is rewarded,"},{"time":313500,"text":"and there are many surprises --"},{"time":315073,"text":"a degree of environmental\nawareness, for instance,"},{"time":318253,"text":"and of humans as mere stewards\nof God's creation,"},{"time":321846,"text":"unmatched in the Bible."},{"time":324349,"text":"And where the Bible is addressed\nexclusively to men,"},{"time":327250,"text":"using the second-\nand third-person masculine,"},{"time":329900,"text":"the Koran includes women --"},{"time":332500,"text":"talking, for instance,"},{"time":333948,"text":"of believing men and believing women,"},{"time":336396,"text":"honorable men and honorable women."},{"time":340984,"text":"Or take the infamous verse\nabout killing the unbelievers."},{"time":345851,"text":"Yes, it does say that,"},{"time":347500,"text":"but in a very specific context:"},{"time":350250,"text":"the anticipated conquest\nof the sanctuary city of Mecca,"},{"time":354611,"text":"where fighting was usually forbidden."},{"time":357159,"text":"And the permission comes\nhedged about with qualifiers."},{"time":360706,"text":"Not \"You must kill unbelievers in Mecca,\""},{"time":363500,"text":"but you can, you are allowed to,"},{"time":365763,"text":"but only after a grace period is over,"},{"time":370158,"text":"and only if there's no other\npact in place,"},{"time":373040,"text":"and only if they try to stop\nyou getting to the Kaaba,"},{"time":376500,"text":"and only if they attack you first."},{"time":379240,"text":"And even then -- God is merciful;"},{"time":382869,"text":"forgiveness is supreme --"},{"time":384922,"text":"and so, essentially,"},{"time":387664,"text":"better if you don't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389141,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":392607,"text":"This was perhaps the biggest surprise --"},{"time":395394,"text":"how flexible the Koran is,"},{"time":397500,"text":"at least in minds that are not\nfundamentally inflexible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402396,"text":"\"Some of these verses\nare definite in meaning,\" it says,"},{"time":406067,"text":"\"and others are ambiguous.\""},{"time":408881,"text":"The perverse at heart\nwill seek out the ambiguities,"},{"time":412707,"text":"trying to create discord\nby pinning down meanings of their own."},{"time":417360,"text":"Only God knows the true meaning."},{"time":421031,"text":"The phrase \"God is subtle\"\nappears again and again,"},{"time":425017,"text":"and indeed, the whole\nof the Koran is far more subtle"},{"time":427643,"text":"than most of us have been led to believe."},{"time":430171,"text":"As in, for instance, that little matter\nof virgins and paradise."},{"time":436444,"text":"Old-fashioned orientalism\ncomes into play here."},{"time":440591,"text":"The word used four times is \"houris,\""},{"time":445193,"text":"rendered as dark-eyed maidens\nwith swelling breasts,"},{"time":449674,"text":"or as fair, high-bosomed virgins."},{"time":453939,"text":"Yet all there is in the original Arabic\nis that one word: houris."},{"time":459245,"text":"Not a swelling breast\nor high bosom in sight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461773,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":464301,"text":"Now this may be a way of saying\n\"pure beings,\" like in angels,"},{"time":468882,"text":"or it may be like\nthe Greek \"kouros\" or \"kore,\""},{"time":471919,"text":"an eternal youth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473285,"text":"But the truth is, nobody really knows."},{"time":476045,"text":"And that's the point."},{"time":478206,"text":"Because the Koran is quite clear"},{"time":480646,"text":"when it says that you'll be\n\"a new creation in paradise,\""},{"time":485500,"text":"and that you will be \"recreated\nin a form unknown to you,\""},{"time":490653,"text":"which seems to me\na far more appealing prospect"},{"time":493212,"text":"than a virgin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494815,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":502992,"text":"And that number 72 never appears."},{"time":506327,"text":"There are no 72 virgins in the Koran."},{"time":510017,"text":"That idea only came\ninto being 300 years later,"},{"time":513286,"text":"and most Islamic scholars\nsee it as the equivalent"},{"time":516287,"text":"of people with wings sitting on clouds\nand strumming harps."},{"time":521333,"text":"Paradise is quite the opposite."},{"time":524851,"text":"It's not virginity;"},{"time":526638,"text":"it's fecundity;"},{"time":528733,"text":"it's plenty."},{"time":530847,"text":"It's gardens watered by running streams."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536260,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537436,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}